  "type": "Chapter",
  "number": "8",
  "title": "Chapter 8",
  "body": " Chapter 8   tension_compression.ggb  Interactive Diagram In this interactive you may change the external forces on this two-force member from tension to compression, and then cut the beam into sections. You will see that each piece must have an internal force to balance the external force. If you move the cut point, you'll see that the value of the internal force is constant at every location.  Interactive 8-1 Source: tension_compression.ggb      bell_crank.ggb  Interactive Diagram This interactive demonstrates how the internal loads at a cut may be represented.  Interactive 8-2 Source: bell_crank.ggb      triangle-load-cut.ggb  Interactive Diagram This interactive allows you to change the cut location on a beam with a downward distributed load varying from a maximum at point to 0 at point . The check box cuts the beam and exposes the internal loadings. Moving point traces out the shear and moment as functions of .  Interactive 8-3 Source: triangle-load-cut.ggb      translate-coord-sys.ggb  Interactive Diagram Notice as you change the slope, global intercept, and location of point that the only values that shift between local and global equations are the intercept values ( vs. ) and the coordinate of .  Interactive 8-4 Source: translate-coord-sys.ggb      VM-building-blocks.ggb  Interactive Diagram Try moving the red dots to change the load and see the effects on the diagrams.  Interactive 8-5 Source: VM-building-blocks.ggb      VM_1.ggb  Interactive Diagram and are the supports. , , and are the loads.  Interactive 8-6 Source: VM_1.ggb      VM_2.ggb   Interactive 8-7 Source: VM_2.ggb      VM_3.ggb  Interactive Diagram and are the reaction forces.  Interactive 8-8 Source: VM_3.ggb      VM_4.ggb  Interactive Diagram and are the reaction forces.  Interactive 8-9 Source: VM_4.ggb      VM_5.ggb  Interactive Diagram The load is a function of . This applet uses the sign convention that positive loads act down, so .  Interactive 8-10 Source: VM_5.ggb     "
