  "id": "interactives-chapter-10",
  "level": "1",
  "url": "interactives-chapter-10.html",
  "type": "Chapter",
  "number": "10",
  "title": "Chapter 10",
  "body": " Chapter 10   moi-potato.ggb   Interactive 10-1 Source: moi-potato.ggb      moi-Ixyz.ggb  Interactive Diagram Click on the labeled rectangle to change the view to show the appropriate differential element to calculate each moment of inertia. Rotate element through space.  Interactive 10-2 Source: moi-Ixyz.ggb      moi-rectangle-diagram.ggb   Interactive 10-3 Source: moi-rectangle-diagram.ggb      triangle-diagram.ggb   Interactive 10-4 Source: triangle-diagram.ggb      moi-circle-interactive.ggb   Interactive 10-5 Source: moi-circle-interactive.ggb      moi-basic-rect.ggb  Interactive Diagram The inteactive calculates the moment of inertia using the parallel axis theorem . Note that a centroidal moment of inertia is smaller than the moment of inertia about any corresponding parallel axis. Move the red dots to change the size and location of the rectangle.  Interactive 10-6 Source: moi-basic-rect.ggb      moi-semicircle.ggb  Interactive Diagram The inteactive calculates the moment of inertia of a semi-circle about three different axes using the parallel axis theorem . The distance term represents the distance between the axis of interest and a parallel axis passing through the centroid of the shape. Move the red dots to change the size and location of the semi-circle.  Interactive 10-7 Source: moi-semicircle.ggb      composite-moi.ggb  Interactive Diagram Demonstrates calculation of the moment of inertia of a composite shape about the axis using the parallel axis theorem . Note that when using the parallel axis theorem, area is always positive, and the MOI of the hole is subtracted from to get the MOI of the combined shape.  Interactive 10-8 Source: composite-moi.ggb     "
